#: ../../manual/modeling/meshes/editing/normals.rst:53
msgid ""
"These commands will recalculate the normals of selected faces so that they "
"point outside (respectively inside) the volume that the face belongs to. "
"This volume do not need to be closed. In fact, this means that the face of "
"interest must be adjacent with at least one non-coplanar other face. For "
"example, with a *Grid* primitive, neither *Recalculate Outside* nor "
"*Recalculate Inside* will never modify its normals..."
msgstr ""
